meditation is it doesn't cost

01:21:10.310 --> 01:21:11.930 align:middle line:90%
anything.

01:21:11.930 --> 01:21:14.510 align:middle line:90%
You can do it anywhere, anytime.

01:21:14.510 --> 01:21:18.080 align:middle line:84%
Just quiet the mind and get rid
of that excess mental baggage.

01:21:18.080 --> 01:21:21.230 align:middle line:90%


01:21:21.230 --> 01:21:23.030 align:middle line:90%
But the mind isn't all bad.

01:21:23.030 --> 01:21:25.160 align:middle line:84%
You can actually
use your imagination

01:21:25.160 --> 01:21:28.280 align:middle line:84%
through visualization to
activate a powerful healing

01:21:28.280 --> 01:21:30.230 align:middle line:90%
response.

01:21:30.230 --> 01:21:36.110 align:middle line:84%
>> What if I told you to do a
simple exercise of imagination,

01:21:36.110 --> 01:21:39.770 align:middle line:84%
to go to your refrigerator,
open it up, find a lemon,

01:21:39.770 --> 01:21:42.080 align:middle line:84%
take the lemon, put it
on the cutting board,

01:21:42.080 --> 01:21:45.260 align:middle line:84%
cut the thing in half,
take a look at it--

01:21:45.260 --> 01:21:47.660 align:middle line:90%
juice is welling up--

01:21:47.660 --> 01:21:50.810 align:middle line:84%
and stick out your
tongue and lick it.

01:21:50.810 --> 01:21:53.780 align:middle line:84%
Your salivary glands
would go crazy,

01:21:53.780 --> 01:21:57.000 align:middle line:84%
and it was all in
your imagination.

01:21:57.000 --> 01:22:01.730 align:middle line:84%
So there's no question
that what we imagine

01:22:01.730 --> 01:22:04.040 align:middle line:90%
can affect our physiology.

01:22:04.040 --> 01:22:06.290 align:middle line:10%
>> For several years, I've
been collecting stories,

01:22:06.290 --> 01:22:10.580 align:middle line:10%
testimonies, interviewing
several hundred people

01:22:10.580 --> 01:22:14.420 align:middle line:10%
who've used visualization as
some part of their healing

01:22:14.420 --> 01:22:15.410 align:middle line:10%
journey.

01:22:15.410 --> 01:22:19.340 align:middle line:84%
And amazingly, what,
like, 99% of them do

01:22:19.340 --> 01:22:22.190 align:middle line:84%
is you take an internal
picture of illness

01:22:22.190 --> 01:22:24.630 align:middle line:84%
and convert it into an
internal picture of wellness.

01:22:24.630 --> 01:22:25.430 align:middle line:90%
And that's it.

01:22:25.430 --> 01:22:26.900 align:middle line:90%
It's illness to wellness.

01:22:26.900 --> 01:22:27.700 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

01:22:27.700 --> 01:22:30.420 align:middle line:84%
And they just do it over
and over and over again.

01:22:30.420 --> 01:22:33.230 align:middle line:84%
So to give you a few examples
of the strategy of illness

01:22:33.230 --> 01:22:37.130 align:middle line:84%
to wellness, people who are even
getting chemotherapy the chemo

01:22:37.130 --> 01:22:39.846 align:middle line:84%
drugs as little piranha
fish going, [MUNCHING]

01:22:39.846 --> 01:22:41.500 align:middle line:90%
and nibbling at the tumor.

01:22:41.500 --> 01:22:43.528 align:middle line:10%
But in their mind's
eye, what they're seeing

01:22:43.528 --> 01:22:46.195 align:middle line:10%
is the tumor getting smaller and
smaller and smaller and smaller

01:22:46.195 --> 01:22:47.420 align:middle line:10%
till it's got.

01:22:47.420 --> 01:22:49.370 align:middle line:84%
People in radiotherapy
imagine the radiation

01:22:49.370 --> 01:22:51.770 align:middle line:84%
that bolts of lightning going
pew, pew, pew, pew, pew,

01:22:51.770 --> 01:22:53.270 align:middle line:84%
and bombing chunks
out of the tumor.

01:22:53.270 --> 01:22:55.830 align:middle line:84%
But again, tumor's getting
smaller and smaller and smaller

01:22:55.830 --> 01:22:56.630 align:middle line:90%
till it's gone.

01:22:56.630 --> 01:23:01.840 align:middle line:90%


01:23:01.840 --> 01:23:05.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Toward the end of the
treatment, I was really weak.

01:23:05.800 --> 01:23:07.790 align:middle line:84%
So Dianne called,
and she said, do you

01:23:07.790 --> 01:23:08.980 align:middle line:90%
want to have your session?

01:23:08.980 --> 01:23:10.647 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I don't
think I can make it.

01:23:10.647 --> 01:23:12.160 align:middle line:90%
I can't really get up.

01:23:12.160 --> 01:23:13.780 align:middle line:90%
I was just laying down a lot.

01:23:13.780 --> 01:23:15.230 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't really get up.

01:23:15.230 --> 01:23:18.160 align:middle line:84%
And so she came to visit
me to give me a session.

01:23:18.160 --> 01:23:21.330 align:middle line:84%
And when she got there,
I was just shaking.

01:23:21.330 --> 01:23:23.370 align:middle line:84%
So she said, I think
you're running a fever.

01:23:23.370 --> 01:23:26.340 align:middle line:84%
She gave me the thermometer,
and it was 103.5.

01:23:26.340 --> 01:23:28.600 align:middle line:84%
So she said, we need to
take you to the hospital.

01:23:28.600 --> 01:23:29.700 align:middle line:84%
So she drove me to
the hospital, and it

01:23:29.700 --> 01:23:30.950 align:middle line:90%
