I did our evaluation--

01:31:31.837 --> 01:31:34.360 align:middle line:84%
>> And even my oncologist,
who I thought was the best

01:31:34.360 --> 01:31:36.332 align:middle line:90%
of the-- that I could find.

01:31:36.332 --> 01:31:38.290 align:middle line:84%
They'd say, wow, it's
amazing, all of your hair

01:31:38.290 --> 01:31:39.830 align:middle line:90%
hasn't come out.

01:31:39.830 --> 01:31:40.630 align:middle line:90%
What are you doing?

01:31:40.630 --> 01:31:41.505 align:middle line:90%
You look really good.

01:31:41.505 --> 01:31:43.510 align:middle line:90%
Your numbers are good and stuff.

01:31:43.510 --> 01:31:45.550 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm
doing wheatgrass.

01:31:45.550 --> 01:31:47.540 align:middle line:84%
And he'd go, oh,
OK, well, whatever.

01:31:47.540 --> 01:31:49.810 align:middle line:84%
And I said, do you not
believe in wheatgrass?

01:31:49.810 --> 01:31:52.935 align:middle line:84%
And he said, no, but if
it makes you feel better.

01:31:52.935 --> 01:31:54.310 align:middle line:84%
They gave me two
different types.

01:31:54.310 --> 01:31:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And with the one, my hair
would have come out completely.

01:31:57.070 --> 01:31:59.930 align:middle line:84%
But with the two, yeah,
for sure, it was a goner.

01:31:59.930 --> 01:32:02.110 align:middle line:90%
And it never all came out.

01:32:02.110 --> 01:32:05.100 align:middle line:84%
I still had a good
2/3 of it at the end.

01:32:05.100 --> 01:32:09.130 align:middle line:10%
>> Love and all the time
in the world to enjoy it.

01:32:09.130 --> 01:32:12.190 align:middle line:84%
>> The best part for me was
that I was supported by friends

01:32:12.190 --> 01:32:16.150 align:middle line:84%
and family and that I had
spiritual therapists that

01:32:16.150 --> 01:32:19.870 align:middle line:84%
really helped me work through
all of this stuff and get rid

01:32:19.870 --> 01:32:25.390 align:middle line:84%
of the fear and the old hurts
and wounds and then allow me

01:32:25.390 --> 01:32:30.370 align:middle line:84%
to return to a really
high state of healing.

01:32:30.370 --> 01:32:33.590 align:middle line:90%


01:32:33.590 --> 01:32:36.680 align:middle line:84%
>> If you perceive that people
are coming to help you and hold

01:32:36.680 --> 01:32:39.530 align:middle line:84%
you and help you through this
process and you feel this

01:32:39.530 --> 01:32:42.560 align:middle line:84%
outpouring of love, they are
actually helping your body

01:32:42.560 --> 01:32:45.110 align:middle line:84%
heal, because as soon
as you perceive that,

01:32:45.110 --> 01:32:48.680 align:middle line:84%
as soon as you believe that
people are sending you love,

01:32:48.680 --> 01:32:50.420 align:middle line:90%
you have this oxytocin response.

01:32:50.420 --> 01:32:52.250 align:middle line:84%
And oxytocin release
has been associated

01:32:52.250 --> 01:32:56.250 align:middle line:84%
with increased natural killer
cells, increased white cells.

01:32:56.250 --> 01:32:58.460 align:middle line:84%
The immune response just
goes through the roof.

01:32:58.460 --> 01:33:01.680 align:middle line:90%


01:33:01.680 --> 01:33:04.740 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really important to
work with doctors that treat you

01:33:04.740 --> 01:33:08.190 align:middle line:84%
as a whole person and surround
yourself with friends that

01:33:08.190 --> 01:33:11.190 align:middle line:84%
inspire hope and strengthen
in you rather than add

01:33:11.190 --> 01:33:13.340 align:middle line:90%
to your fear.

01:33:13.340 --> 01:33:15.812 align:middle line:84%
It's hard, though, because
when I'm sick or in pain,

01:33:15.812 --> 01:33:18.020 align:middle line:84%
I feel vulnerable and just
want to crawl up in a ball

01:33:18.020 --> 01:33:19.590 align:middle line:90%
and be alone.

01:33:19.590 --> 01:33:22.200 align:middle line:84%
So how do we break out of
that downward spiral of fear?

01:33:22.200 --> 01:33:27.580 align:middle line:84%
How do we transcend the pain
and shift to a positive mindset?

01:33:27.580 --> 01:33:30.290 align:middle line:84%
>> So when a person shows
up in a doctor's office

01:33:30.290 --> 01:33:33.650 align:middle line:84%
and they're given the diagnosis
of rheumatoid arthritis or MS

01:33:33.650 --> 01:33:38.300 align:middle line:84%
or cancer or diabetes, once
they hear that diagnosis,

01:33:38.300 --> 01:33:42.410 align:middle line:84%
the common emotions they
experience is either fear

01:33:42.410 --> 01:33:43.430 align:middle line:90%
or sadness.

01:33:43.430 --> 01:33:46.460 align:middle line:84%
They can think
positively all they want.

01:33:46.460 --> 01:33:49.820 align:middle line:84%
They can say, I'm going to
overcome this condition.

01:33:49.820 --> 01:33:53.300 align:middle line:84%
But if they are feeling
fear, that thought never

01:33:53.300 --> 01:33:55.670 align:middle line:84%
makes it past the
brainstem into the body

01:33:55.670 --> 01:33:58.190 align:middle line:84%
because it's not in
alignment with the body's

01:33:58.190 --> 01:33:59.810 align:middle line:90%
emotional state.

01:33:59.810 --> 01:34:03.350 align:middle line:84%
You get that person to
change their emotional state

01:34:03.350 --> 01:34:05.260 align:middle line:84%
and get them into a
state of gratitude.

01:34:05.260 --> 01:34:06.830 align:middle line:90%
Why gratitude?

01:34:06.830 --> 01:34:11.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, we normally give
thanks when we get something.

01:34:11.120 --> 01:34:14.210 align:middle line:84%
But if you're giving thanks
in a state of gratitude,

01:34:14.210 --> 01:34:16.670 align:middle line:84%
your body is believing
it's receiving something

01:34:16.670 --> 01:34:18.980 align:middle line:84%
because the emotional
signature of gratitude

01:34:18.980 --> 01:34:20.385 align:middle line:90%
means it's already happened.

01:34:20.385 --> 01:34:22.920 align:middle line:90%


01:34:22.920 --> 01:34:27.470 align:middle line:84%
>> So the more that we can feel
the feeling as if our healing

01:34:27.470 --> 01:34:32.000 align:middle line:84%
has already occurred, giving
thanks for that healing already

01:34:32.000 --> 01:34:36.650 align:middle line:84%
being present, that is the
trigger for our bodies to grow

01:34:36.650 --> 01:34:39.650 align:middle line:84%
the nerve cells to make
the connections to trigger

01:34:39.650 --> 01:34:42.680 align:middle line:84%
the brain chemistry to
reflect that healing.

01:34:42.680 --> 01:34:45.440 align:middle line:90%


01:34:45.440 --> 01:34:48.290 align:middle line:84%
We have this advanced
nervous system

01:34:48.290 --> 01:34:51.170 align:middle line:84%
that we regulate
through the choices

01:34:51.170 --> 01:34:55.670 align:middle line:84%
we make in our lives of
what we think, what we feel,

01:34:55.670 --> 01:34:58.670 align:middle line:84%
what we believe,
and specifically

01:34:58.670 --> 01:35:03.200 align:middle line:84%
the emotions that we
choose to respond to what

01:35:03.200 --> 01:35:04.390 align:middle line:90%
life brings to our doorstep.

01:35:04.390 --> 01:35:11.580 align:middle line:90%


01:35:11.580 --> 01:35:14.170 align:middle line:84%
>> You know, I've been trying
not to take the steroids.

01:35:14.170 --> 01:35:14.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

01:35:14.970 --> 01:35:17.360 align:middle line:84%
>> So I went through a
small breakout last month,

01:35:17.360 --> 01:35:19.200 align:middle line:90%
which I thought was good.

01:35:19.200 --> 01:35:21.010 align:middle line:84%
And then it was kind
of just dormant.

01:35:21.010 --> 01:35:22.930 align:middle line:90%
Like, it never really went away.

01:35:22.930 --> 01:35:25.550 align:middle line:84%
And then it all of a sudden
just exploded over the weekend.

01:35:25.550 --> 01:35:26.350 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

01:35:26.350 --> 01:35:29.120 align:middle line:84%
>> So I have, like, these
massive boils that are

01:35:29.120 --> 01:35:31.740 align:middle line:84%
starting, and then I have
them all over my chest.

01:35:31.740 --> 01:35:33.010 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

01:35:33.010 --> 01:35:33.810 align:middle line:90%
Oh my God.

01:35:33.810 --> 01:35:34.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

01:35:34.610 --> 01:35:35.470 align:middle line:90%
>> So that's like--

01:35:35.470 --> 01:35:37.600 align:middle line:84%
>> This is like when
it's almost full blown.

01:35:37.600 --> 01:35:39.670 align:middle line:90%
It's not quite.

01:35:39.670 --> 01:35:42.635 align:middle line:84%
>> So if you have
something residing in you--

01:35:42.635 --> 01:35:45.010 align:middle line:84%
like, say you have Epstein-Barr
virus or say you have one

01:35:45.010 --> 01:35:46.240 align:middle line:90%
of the shingles viruses--

01:35:46.240 --> 01:35:47.770 align:middle line:90%
stress can trigger it.

01:35:47.770 --> 01:35:49.420 align:middle line:90%
Mold can trigger it.

01:35:49.420 --> 01:35:52.060 align:middle line:84%
Someone breaking your
trust can trigger it.

01:35:52.060 --> 01:35:54.640 align:middle line:84%
Problems at work can trigger
it, being fired from your job--

01:35:54.640 --> 01:35:56.480 align:middle line:90%
everything can trigger it.

01:35:56.480 --> 01:35:59.290 align:middle line:84%
But there has to be something
in there to trigger.

01:35:59.290 --> 01:36:01.160 align:middle line:84%
The key is knowing
what the real cause

01:36:01.160 --> 01:36:03.400 align:middle line:84%
is so you can live life
like a normal person

01:36:03.400 --> 01:36:09.110 align:middle line:84%
and have things go wrong and
not go down because of it.

01:36:09.110 --> 01:36:12.570 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, so my little flower
blossoms are turning into big

01:36:12.570 --> 01:36:14.070 align:middle line:90%
dahlias.

01:36:14.070 --> 01:36:17.570 align:middle line:84%
They're starting to
merge together and get

01:36:17.570 --> 01:36:23.060 align:middle line:84%
really huge and extremely
painful and hot,

01:36:23.060 --> 01:36:27.150 align:middle line:84%
constantly burning up and
then getting the chills.

01:36:27.150 --> 01:36:28.550 align:middle line:90%
Powered through the day.

01:36:28.550 --> 01:36:42.010 align:middle line:90%


01:36:42.010 --> 01:36:43.960 align:middle line:84%
They immediately
called some doctors

01:36:43.960 --> 01:36:45.460 align:middle line:84%
and put me in
isolation because they

01:36:45.460 --> 01:36:48.760 align:middle line:84%
didn't know if it
was contagious,

01:36:48.760 --> 01:36:53.210 align:middle line:84%
viral, what was
going on, infectious.

01:36:53.210 --> 01:36:56.210 align:middle line:84%
I had some really
bad abdominal pains

01:36:56.210 --> 01:37:02.110 align:middle line:84%
and just this is just getting
so painful and intense.

01:37:02.110 --> 01:37:03.730 align:middle line:84%
So they called all
those specialists,

01:37:03.730 --> 01:37:06.340 align:middle line:84%
and they ran all these tests,
and everything came back

01:37:06.340 --> 01:37:07.180 align:middle line:90%
basically normal.

01:37:07.180 --> 01:37:10.330 align:middle line:90%


01:37:10.330 --> 01:37:13.243 align:middle line:84%
You know, as I got out, they
gave me just really heavy doses

01:37:13.243 --> 01:37:14.910 align:middle line:84%
of steroids to knock
it out because they

01:37:14.910 --> 01:37:17.580 align:middle line:84%
could see that I wasn't
getting better on its own.

01:37:17.580 --> 01:37:19.470 align:middle line:84%
And then my dermatologist
was concerned

01:37:19.470 --> 01:37:23.040 align:middle line:84%
about me taking the steroids
after to initially knock out

01:37:23.040 --> 01:37:26.640 align:middle line:84%
the breakout, so she gave me
a prescription of Dapsone,

01:37:26.640 --> 01:37:27.900 align:middle line:90%
which is an antibiotic.

01:37:27.900 --> 01:37:30.868 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't realize the
strength of the antibiotic

01:37:30.868 --> 01:37:32.160 align:middle line:90%
until I went to the pharmacist.

01:37:32.160 --> 01:37:33.743 align:middle line:84%
He stopped me at the
counter and said,

01:37:33.743 --> 01:37:37.050 align:middle line:84%
do you know that this is a
really heavy dose of antibiotic

01:37:37.050 --> 01:37:38.190 align:middle line:90%
that you're taking?

01:37:38.190 --> 01:37:39.368 align:middle line:90%
So that's where I'm at.

01:37:39.368 --> 01:37:40.410 align:middle line:90%
I have to pick my poison.

01:37:40.410 --> 01:37:43.080 align:middle line:84%
Do I Band-Aid it
with steroids or do

01:37:43.080 --> 01:37:46.205 align:middle line:84%
I take this heavy
antibiotic indefinitely?

01:37:46.205 --> 01:37:51.060 align:middle line:90%


01:37:51.060 --> 01:37:55.380 align:middle line:84%
Being in LA and going to some of
the best doctors in their field

01:37:55.380 --> 01:37:58.860 align:middle line:84%
and probably seeing half a
dozen to a dozen doctors now,

01:37:58.860 --> 01:38:00.448 align:middle line:90%
nobody can figure it out.

01:38:00.448 --> 01:38:02.490 align:middle line:84%
They give me drugs for
all these different things

01:38:02.490 --> 01:38:03.650 align:middle line:90%
that they think it may be.

01:38:03.650 --> 01:38:05.570 align:middle line:84%
But, I mean, that's kind of the
process with Western medicine.

01:38:05.570 --> 01:38:07.200 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult
because it's just

01:38:07.200 --> 01:38:08.617 align:middle line:84%
let's just throw
everything at it,

01:38:08.617 --> 01:38:10.630 align:middle line:90%
and which one Velcros the best?

01:38:10.630 --> 01:38:12.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think that if
alternative doctors were

01:38:12.630 --> 01:38:17.220 align:middle line:84%
covered by insurance you might
go more often or they might

01:38:17.220 --> 01:38:18.110 align:middle line:90%
seem more credible?

01:38:18.110 --> 01:38:20.610 align:middle line:84%
>> Definitely, because I know
with steroids, it's very easy.

01:38:20.610 --> 01:38:22.645 align:middle line:84%
It's $5, I get it,
and I'm better.

01:38:22.645 --> 01:38:24.270 align:middle line:84%
If I could get access
to these vitamins

01:38:24.270 --> 01:38:28.890 align:middle line:84%
and to these alternative
doctors at those nominal costs,

01:38:28.890 --> 01:38:30.840 align:middle line:84%
then I would probably
go much more often.

01:38:30.840 --> 01:38:36.880 align:middle line:90%


01:38:36.880 --> 01:38:39.700 align:middle line:84%
I believe the
naturopath and all that

01:38:39.700 --> 01:38:41.730 align:middle line:84%
and doing everything
that's alternative.

01:38:41.730 --> 01:38:43.460 align:middle line:84%
I just can't seem
to dedicate myself.

01:38:43.460 --> 01:38:44.260 align:middle line:90%
I don't know why.

01:38:44.260 --> 01:38:47.487 align:middle line:90%


01:38:47.487 --> 01:38:49.780 align:middle line:84%
You know, maybe I'm
just emotionally

01:38:49.780 --> 01:38:52.270 align:middle line:84%
stunted to do or open
myself up to that

01:38:52.270 --> 01:38:54.313 align:middle line:84%
or there's just something
that's blocking me,

01:38:54.313 --> 01:38:55.480 align:middle line:90%
because it seems achievable.

01:38:55.480 --> 01:38:57.242 align:middle line:84%
And in my condition,
I should be able to.

01:38:57.242 --> 01:38:58.450 align:middle line:90%
But for some reason, I can't.

01:38:58.450 --> 01:39:09.880 align:middle line:90%


01:39:09.880 --> 01:39:13.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Eva made me realize how much
courage and sometimes cost it

01:39:13.060 --> 01:39:16.150 align:middle line:84%
takes to commit to a
holistic path of healing.

01:39:16.150 --> 01:39:17.980 align:middle line:84%
As a society, we've
been conditioned

01:39:17.980 --> 01:39:20.530 align:middle line:84%
to believe that conventional
doctors know best

01:39:20.530 --> 01:39:22.060 align:middle line:90%
and that convenience is key.

01:39:22.060 --> 01:39:22.525 align:middle line:90%
>> --hurt me so much.

01:39:22.525 --> 01:39:23.455 align:middle line:90%
>> --has hurt me so much.

01:39:23.455 --> 01:39:23.920 align:middle line:90%
>> I had no idea.

01:39:23.920 --> 01:39:24.850 align:middle line:90%
>> I had no idea.

01:39:24.850 --> 01:39:27.710 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, though, it's
either pay now or pay later.

01:39:27.710 --> 01:39:29.680 align:middle line:84%
And I really fear
the long-term effects

01:39:29.680 --> 01:39:31.980 align:middle line:84%
the steroids will
have on Eva's body.

01:39:31.980 --> 01:39:33.640 align:middle line:84%
But I truly understand
her struggle.

01:39:33.640 --> 01:39:37.180 align:middle line:84%
So all I can do is continue to
support her in any way I can

01:39:37.180 --> 01:39:38.780 align:middle line:84%
and pray she finds
an answer soon.

01:39:38.780 --> 01:39:45.350 align:middle line:90%


01:39:45.350 --> 01:39:48.530 align:middle line:84%
It's around your third
anniversary being cancer free.

01:39:48.530 --> 01:39:50.810 align:middle line:84%
Some fear comes up
around this time of year

01:39:50.810 --> 01:39:52.030 align:middle line:90%
because you've heard stories.

01:39:52.030 --> 01:39:53.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, so many.

01:39:53.120 --> 01:39:56.120 align:middle line:84%
When I first went back
to work, they'd say, oh,

01:39:56.120 --> 01:39:58.640 align:middle line:84%
great to have you back,
and then say, yeah,

01:39:58.640 --> 01:40:01.760 align:middle line:84%
my so-and-so had
cancer, and then--

01:40:01.760 --> 01:40:02.695 align:middle line:90%
oh, they were great.

01:40:02.695 --> 01:40:04.070 align:middle line:84%
They did the chemo,
and then they

01:40:04.070 --> 01:40:05.255 align:middle line:90%
had no cancer for two years.

01:40:05.255 --> 01:40:07.880 align:middle line:84%
And then 2 and 1/2 years later,
